The high quality ones were made at the government armories at the Taku Naval Dockyard Arsenal(some of which are so marked), the Sichang Arsenal, the Hanyang Arsenal and the Shanxi (Shansei) Arsenal. There are no Mauser markings on this one nor any Chinese markings but the pistol was brought into the USA from China (no import marks). Fully functional and all matching serial numbers. Serial number on this pistol falls within the range of serial numbers associated with the Taku arsenal for the Flatside versions manufactured there. May wish to have the barrel relined for shooting (prices run $80 to $195 depending on who you use). A rare pistol at a great price.

title: For Sale:  Brand New Custom AR15 Matched Set- Rifle & Pistol in 300 AAC Blackout
location: Northern NH, New Hampshire, United States
postcontent:
I need to buy my wife a house closer to her work and to do so, I must unfortunately sell off some of my collection. 
So here goes:

Up for sale is my custom built matching set of AR's in 300 AAC Blackout. These are brand new and never fired and are completely set up and ready to go. These are not your typical basic AR's or anything that any of your buddies will have when you pull them out at the range and I'd be willing to bet that you won't see another custom pair like this again either! These are also sequentially numbered serial numbers on the lowers.

To start off, both of these are sitting on customized Daytona Defense and Tactical skeletonized "Reaper" lowers with matching DDT trigger guards. They're 7075 T-6 aluminum with Mil-spec Type III hard coat and anodized black. For customization, these lowers have no roll pins in them at all. The Bolt Catch pins have been drilled and tapped and fitted with screw-in type pins from Windham Weaponry like most AR10's. The trigger guards have been set screwed. There is a set screw under each trigger to adjust the up take or "creep" of them. The spring and detent for the rear take-down pins have been set screwed and are now captive. Both lowers are sporting Rock River Arms 2 stage National Match trigger groups, they're both very smooth triggers with crisp, clean sharp breaks. 

The uppers are both FN's produced for them under contract by the Brass Aluminum Forging Enterprises foundry. They're also 7075 T-6 aluminum with Type III hard coat anodize. The uppers have been shimmed and Accu-wedged and sit nice and tight to the lowers like they were machined and matched together. They are both M4 flat top uppers with the M4 feed ramps and T marks and forward assists. They're both running MPI and HP tested AR15 semi-auto bolt carrier groups.

Both of these have matching flip-up poly sights, ambi sling loop receiver end plates and single point adjustable bungie type slings.

The carbine is a 16" heavy barrel in Phosphate with a 1/8 twist. It has a micro gas block and a Melonited gas tube under its 10" free float quad rail with end cap. It has a Mil-spec 6 position adjustable stock with a USGI rubber butt pad. It also comes with a 30 round Lancer smoked translucent L5-AWM hybrid battle mag.

The matching pistol is a 7.5" heavy barrel also in Phosphate with a 1/8 twist. It also has a micro gas block with a stainless steel gas tube sitting under its matching 7" free floating quad rail with end cap. The pistol however does come with a brand new but oh-so controversial new style Sig Sauer SBX arm brace. This pistol also includes a 20 round Lancer smoked translucent L5-AWM hybrid battle mag.

These custom builds feature ALL American, USA made quality parts! No crappy, inferior Chinese parts here! These are some of the coolest custom builds that you'll find out there and I guarantee that none of your buddies will have these and they will be drooling over them too when they see them!!

For this matched set of sequentially serial numbered AR's, carbine and pistol together with all the customization and accessories I am asking $3400.00 or best reasonable offer.  I do not want to split up this set. I do not want trades, trades won't help me get the wife a house!

I would prefer to sell these as transferred through an FFL with the buyer to pick up the transfer fees, but if the buyer is a NH resident, these can be sold face to face with a bill of sale and your valid NH driver's license. Any out of state buyer, please be prepared to cover the shipping and FFL transfer fees to your local dealer.

Thank you for viewing my listing and for any questions, please feel free to ask away.

Oh and by the way, if you're looking for something a little more traditional in the AR platform, and for a little bit less money, I also have a matching sequentially numbered set of these in .223 Wylde. As some may not know, the Wylde set ups will fire both 5.56 NATO and .223 Remington and are actually more accurate with both rounds than the standard 5.56 or .223 barrels. If interested, please feel free to ask me about them.
